  "description": "The bird's plumage was very bright -- head blue-gray, contrasting with the bright green nape, back, and rump. The head had bright white spectacles, bright white chin and throat, with a sharp contrast between throat and auriculars; dark gray bill. The breast and belly were bright white and the flanks were strongly washed bright yellow. Both the primaries and secondaries were edged green. The rectrices were dusky with R6 edged white, R1-R5 edged green.Behaviors: N/A - bird in the handCall: nonePlumage: adult basic",
